<paragraph id="CC63369EB62AFFBDFF048537FD82D2CB" blockId="5.[151,1436,583,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
The keys to Turkish microphthalmous species in 
<bibRefCitation id="A84D4B6FB62AFFBDFD468537FCF5D22F" author="Assing, V." box="[725,882,583,609]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" pagination="375 - 389" refId="ref5045" refString="Assing, V. (2001) A revision of the microphthalmous Lathrobium Gravenhorst of Turkey, with descriptions of two new Lathrobium species from Italy and Albania (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums Wien, 103 B, 375 - 389." type="journal article" year="2001">Assing (2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A84D4B6FB62AFFBDFC128537FC3CD22F" author="Assing, V." box="[897,955,583,609]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref5096" refString="Assing, V. (2007) A revision of the microphthalmous Lathrobium species of Turkey II. Two new species and an additional record of L. brignolii (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). Entomological Problems, 37, 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="2007">2007</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="A84D4B6FB62AFFBDFC6C8537FB08D22F" author="Anlas, S." box="[1023,1167,583,609]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" pagination="1" refId="ref4876" refString="Anlas, S. (2018) A new species and additional records of the microphthalmous Lathrobium species of Turkey (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). Zootaxa, 4527 (1), 097 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4527.1.8" type="journal article" year="2018">Anlaş (2018</bibRefCitation>
, 2021) are modified to include the newly descibed taxa:
</paragraph>
<key id="B84D61AFB62AFFBDFF0485D9FA1BD605" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<keyStep id="77282E3BB62AFFBDFF0485D9FA1BD295" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62AFFBDFF0485D9FA1BD2F0" blockId="5.[151,1437,681,1612]" box="[151,1436,681,703]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="772D95ABB62AFFBDFF0485D9FA1BD2F0" box="[151,1436,681,703]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFF0485D9FF2DD2F0" bold="true" box="[151,170,681,702]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">1.</emphasis>
Eyes strongly reduced, without ommatidia.................................................................. 
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFA0385D9FA1BD2F0" bold="true" box="[1424,1436,681,702]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">2</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62AFFBDFF0485B6FA1BD295" blockId="5.[151,1437,681,1612]" box="[151,1436,710,732]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="772D95ABB62AFFBDFF0485B6FA1BD295" box="[151,1436,710,732]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFF0485B6FF24D295" bold="true" box="[151,163,710,731]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">–</emphasis>
Eyes weakly reduced, with&gt; 30 ommatidia................................................................. 
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFA0385B6FA1BD295" bold="true" box="[1424,1436,710,731]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">6</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="77282E3BB62AFFBDFF048593FA1BD358" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62AFFBDFF048593FA1BD2B6" blockId="5.[151,1437,681,1612]" box="[151,1436,739,762]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="772D95ABB62AFFBDFF048593FA1BD2B6" box="[151,1436,739,762]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFF048593FF2ED2B6" bold="true" box="[151,169,739,760]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">2.</emphasis>
Aedeagus almost symmetrical.......................................................................... 
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFA198593FA1BD2B6" bold="true" box="[1418,1436,739,760]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">3.</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62AFFBDFF048471FA1BD358" blockId="5.[151,1437,681,1612]" box="[151,1436,769,791]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="772D95ABB62AFFBDFF048471FA1BD358" box="[151,1436,769,791]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFF048471FF24D358" bold="true" box="[151,163,769,790]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">–</emphasis>
Aaedeagus strongly asymmetrical........................................................................ 
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFA198471FA1BD358" bold="true" box="[1418,1436,769,790]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">5.</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="77282E3BB62AFFBDFF04846EFA1BD320" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62AFFBDFF04846EFA1BD31F" blockId="5.[151,1437,681,1612]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="772D95ABB62AFFBDFF04846EFA1BD31F" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFF04846EFF2ED37D" bold="true" box="[151,169,798,819]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">3.</emphasis>
Male sternum VII with extensive clusters of dark setae, posterior incision of male sternum VIII distinctly asymmetrical. Distribution: 
<collectingRegion id="0E18F87CB62AFFBDFEF2844CFE37D31F" box="[353,432,828,849]" country="Turkey" name="Amasya" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">Amasya</collectingRegion>
(present paper: figs 10‒18)............................................ 
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFB47844CFA1BD31F" bold="true" box="[1236,1436,827,849]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<taxonomicName id="0BDC4D1DB62AFFBDFB47844CFAE7D31E" authority="Anlaş, 2022" authorityName="Anlaş" authorityYear="2022" box="[1236,1376,827,849]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amasiacum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFB47844CFAE7D31E" bold="true" box="[1236,1376,827,849]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">L. amasiacum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E59B57F7B62AFFBDFAF5844CFA1BD31F" box="[1382,1436,828,849]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62AFFBDFF048429FA1BD320" blockId="5.[151,1437,681,1612]" box="[151,1436,857,879]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="772D95ABB62AFFBDFF048429FA1BD320" box="[151,1436,857,879]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFF048429FF24D320" bold="true" box="[151,163,857,878]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">–</emphasis>
Male sternum VII without clusters of dark setae, posterior incision of male sternum VIII symmetrical.................. 
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFA198429FA1BD320" bold="true" box="[1418,1436,857,878]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">4.</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="77282E3BB62AFFBDFF048406FA1BD3AD" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62AFFBDFF048406FA1BD3E7" blockId="5.[151,1437,681,1612]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="772D95ABB62AFFBDFF048406FA1BD3E7" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFF048406FF2ED3C5" bold="true" box="[151,169,886,907]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">4.</emphasis>
Posterior incision of male sternite VIII deeper, aedeagus larger, 
<quantity id="0B249B7BB62AFFBDFCD38406FC4BD3C2" box="[832,972,886,908]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.145" metricValueMax="1.18" metricValueMin="1.11" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" unit="mm" value="1.145" valueMax="1.18" valueMin="1.11">1.11‒1.18 mm</quantity>
, with a small protrusion apically in ventral view; female sternite VIII strongly modified. Distribution: 
<collectingRegion id="0E18F87CB62AFFBDFD4F84E4FC95D3E4" box="[732,786,916,938]" country="Turkey" name="Tokat" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">Tokat</collectingRegion>
(present paper: figs 1‒9).................. 
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFB7B84E4FA1BD3E7" bold="true" box="[1256,1436,915,937]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<taxonomicName id="0BDC4D1DB62AFFBDFB7B84E4FAE7D3E7" authority="Anlaş, 2022" authorityName="Anlaş" authorityYear="2022" box="[1256,1376,915,937]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tokatense" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFB7B84E4FAE7D3E7" bold="true" box="[1256,1376,915,937]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">L. tokatense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E59B57F7B62AFFBDFAF584E4FA1BD3E7" box="[1382,1436,916,937]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62AFFBDFF0484C1FA1BD3AD" blockId="5.[151,1437,681,1612]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="772D95ABB62AFFBDFF0484C1FA1BD3AD" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFF0484C1FF24D388" bold="true" box="[151,163,945,966]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">–</emphasis>
Posterior incision of male sternite VIII shallower, aedeagus smaller, 
<quantity id="0B249B7BB62AFFBDFCE584C1FB83D388" box="[886,1028,945,967]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.25" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" unit="mm" value="0.825" valueMax="0.85" valueMin="0.8">0.80‒0.85 mm</quantity>
, and bifid apically in ventral view; female sternite VIII weakly modified. Distribution: 
<collectingRegion id="0E18F87CB62AFFBDFD1F84BEFD3AD3AA" box="[652,701,974,996]" country="Turkey" name="Ordu" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">Ordu</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A84D4B6FB62AFFBDFD5984BEFCC9D3AD" author="Assing, V." box="[714,846,974,996]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" pagination="375 - 389" refId="ref5045" refString="Assing, V. (2001) A revision of the microphthalmous Lathrobium Gravenhorst of Turkey, with descriptions of two new Lathrobium species from Italy and Albania (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums Wien, 103 B, 375 - 389." type="journal article" year="2001">Assing, 2001</bibRefCitation>
: figs 30−36)................. 
<taxonomicName id="0BDC4D1DB62AFFBDFB0584BFFA1BD3AD" authority="Bordoni, 1980" authorityName="Bordoni" authorityYear="1980" box="[1174,1436,974,996]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brignolii">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFB0584BFFA1BD3AD" bold="true" box="[1174,1436,974,996]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFB0584BFFA81D3AA" bold="true" box="[1174,1286,974,996]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">L. brignolii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A84D4B6FB62AFFBDFA9F84BEFA1BD3AD" author="Bordoni, A." box="[1292,1436,974,996]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" pagination="75 - 82" refId="ref5193" refString="Bordoni, A. (1980) Studi sui Paederinae. VI. Nuove specie del mediterraneo orientale. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali e del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale in Milano, 121, 75 - 82." type="journal article" year="1980">Bordoni, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="77282E3BB62AFFBDFF04849CFA1BD416" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<paragraph id="CC63369EB62AFFBDFF04849CFA1BD450" blockId="5.[151,1437,681,1612]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="772D95ABB62AFFBDFF04849CFA1BD450" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="FEA8EA8CB62AFFBDFF04849CFF2ED44F" bold="true" box="[151,169,1004,1025]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">5.</emphasis>
Head with pronounced microreticulation; pronotum narrower in relation to head; posterior incision of male sternite VIII shallower, aedeagus smaller, 
<quantity id="0B249B7BB62AFFBDFE698379FD0FD450" box="[506,648,1033,1055]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" unit="mm" value="0.625" valueMax="0.65" valueMin="0.6">0.60–0.65 mm</quantity>
. Distribution: 
<collectingRegion id="0E18F87CB62AFFBDFC818379FC02D451" box="[786,901,1033,1055]" country="Turkey" name="Gumushane" pageId="5" pageNumber="221">Gümüşhane</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A84D4B6FB62AFFBDFC028379FB92D450" author="Assing, V." box="[913,1045,1033,1055]" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref5096" refString="Assing, V. (2007) A revision of the microphthalmous Lathrobium species of Turkey II. Two new species and an additional record of L. brignolii (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). Entomological Problems, 37, 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="2007">Assing, 2007</bibRefCitation>
: figs 1−12).. 
<taxonomicName id="0BDC4D1DB62AFFBDFB0E8379FA1BD450" authority="Assing, 2007" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2007" box="[1181,1436,1032,1055]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distortum">
